-- Asian Stocks Fall for Second Day, Extend Global Decline on U.S. Confidence
-- Darren Boey
-- 2010-06-30T00:09:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/asian-stocks-fall-for-second-day-extend-global-decline-on-u-s-confidence.html

          
          
             Asian stocks fell for a second day,
extending a global rout, as a slump in U.S. consumer confidence
fueled concerns about the strength of the global economy.   
 The MSCI Asia Pacific Index sank 1.4 percent to 112.37 as
of 9:07 a.m. in Tokyo. The Nikkei 225 Stock Average dropped 2
percent, while South Koreaâ€™s Kospi declined 1.9 percent.  
          
          


  


        